solution:
Tension in the wire, $\mathrm{T}=\left(\frac{2 \mathrm{mM}}{\mathrm{m}+\mathrm{M}}\right) \mathrm{g}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
\text { Stress } &=\frac{\text { Force } / \text { Tension }}{\text { Area }}=\frac{2 \mathrm{mM}}{\mathrm{A}(\mathrm{m}+\mathrm{M})} \mathrm{g} \\
&=\frac{2(\mathrm{~m} \times 2 \mathrm{~m}) \mathrm{g}}{\mathrm{A}(\mathrm{m}+2 \mathrm{~m})}(\mathrm{M}=2 \mathrm{~m} \text { given }) \\
&=\frac{4 \mathrm{~m}^2}{3 \mathrm{~mA}} \mathrm{~g}=\frac{4 \mathrm{mg}}{3 \mathrm{~A}}
\end{aligned}
$$
